  "name": "Morrison VAD Hemolysis CFD — Minimal Profile Credibility Package",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to estimate hemolysis indices for centrifugal blood pump designs under ventricular assist device operating conditions. The CFD hemolysis prediction framework employs a power-law damage accumulation model calibrated against the FDA generic centrifugal pump benchmark. Uncertainty quantification via Monte Carlo sampling was performed across inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity. Thirteen credibility factors were evaluated under ASME V&V 40-2018 at Model Risk Level 5. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite the gaps, the overall credibility posture was deemed sufficient for the intended regulatory submission context given the low-risk decision tier assigned by the project sponsor. No structured Context of Use record is attached to this package; intended-use scope is conveyed through the narrative above.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-cfd-2026",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-prediction",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-powerlaw",
