      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) directly maps to the clinical endpoint of red blood cell damage used in device labeling.",
      "rationale": "NIH is computed but its link to the specific clinical endpoint in the device labeling claim is not formally documented. The mapping is assumed rather than demonstrated."
